# Smart Health Monitor
## Overview
This project is an ESP32-based health monitoring system that measures:
- Heart rate (BPM)
- Motion/activity level
- Finger detection status
The collected data is displayed on an OLED screen and uploaded to ThingSpeak for remote monitoring.

## Hardware:
### ESP32
Main controller responsible for sensor reading, processing, display updates, and cloud communication.

### MAX30102
Optical heart rate sensor used to measure pulse and detect finger presence.

### MPU6050
3-axis accelerometer used to detect body movement and classify activity:
- Sitting
- Walking
- Running

### SSD1306 OLED Display
Displays:
- Heart rate (BPM)
- Measurement countdown
- Activity status

## Connections
### I2C Bus
All devices share the same I2C bus.
Device       --  Address 
MAX30102     --    0x57 
MPU6050      --    0x68 
SSD1306 OLED --    0x3C 

### ESP32 Wiring
ESP32 ------ Device 
------------------
GPIO 8  SDA  ---  GPIO 9  SCL 
3.3V  VCC    ---  GND  GND 

## Software Architecture
The application runs multiple FreeRTOS tasks:

### Pulse Task
- Reads MAX30102 data
- Detects finger presence
- Calculates heart rate (BPM)

### Motion Task
- Reads MPU6050 acceleration data
- Classifies activity level

### Display Task
- Updates OLED display
- Shows BPM and activity status

### ThingSpeak Task
- Sends sensor data to ThingSpeak every 15 seconds

## Data Upload

The following values are uploaded to ThingSpeak:

Field ----------  Data 
Field 1 --> Heart Rate (BPM) 
Field 2 --> Motion State
Field 3 --> Finger Detection

Motion state values:
- 0 = Sitting
- 1 = Walking
- 2 = Running

## Development Environment
- ESP-IDF
- FreeRTOS
- C Programming Language

## Features
- Real-time heart rate monitoring
- Motion detection
- OLED display interface
- Wi-Fi connectivity
- Multi-tasking with FreeRTOS
- ThingSpeak cloud integration